1. $\checkmark$ (a) Determine the fifth term of the binomial expansion of $(3 x+4 y)^{16}$ and evaluate its value at $x=\frac{1}{3}$ and $y=\frac{1}{4}$.
(b) Obtain the first three terms in the binomial expansion of $(8-x)^{\frac{1}{3}}$. State the range of $x$ for which the expansion is valid.
(c) The resonant frequency of a series circuit is given by $f=\frac{1}{2 \pi} \frac{1}{\sqrt{\mathrm{LC}}}$, where L is inductance, C is capacitance. Use binomial theorem to determine the approximate change in $f$ if L increases by $1 \%$ and C decreases by $2 \%$.
(2. (a) Given that $\alpha$ and $\beta$ are the roots of the equation $a x^{2}+b x+c=0$ where $a, b$ and $c$ are constants. Express in terms of $a, b$ and $c$.
(i) $\alpha^{2}+\beta^{2}$;
(ii) $\frac{1}{\alpha^{2}}+\frac{1}{\beta^{2}}$.
(b) Solve the equation by using formula method:
$$\frac{1}{(x-3)}+\frac{4}{(x-1)}=2$$
(c) By applying Kirchoff's law to a d.c network, the following simultaneous equations are obtained:
$$\begin{aligned}
& 2 \mathrm{I}_{1}-3 \mathrm{I}_{2}+\mathrm{I}_{3}=4 \\
& 3 \mathrm{I}_{1}+2 \mathrm{I}_{2}-2 \mathrm{I}_{3}=2 \\
& 4 \mathrm{I}_{1}-\mathrm{I}_{2}+3 \mathrm{I}_{3}=16
\end{aligned}$$

Use substitution method to determine the values of the currents, correct to 2 decimal places.
3. (a) Simplify:
(i) $\left(\frac{1}{x}-\frac{1}{y}\right) \div \frac{\left(y^{2}-x^{2}\right)}{x^{2} y^{2}}$
(ii) $\quad \log _{\frac{1}{2}} 8+\log _{2}\left(\frac{1}{8}\right)+\log _{3}\left(\frac{1}{9}\right)$.
(b) Solve the equations:
(i) $5\left(5^{\log 10 x}\right)+5^{(2-\log n a x)}=30$;
(ii) $\quad \log _{4} x-2 \log _{x} 4=1$.
