(i) $7 \operatorname{Sin} \phi+4 \operatorname{Cos} \phi$ in the form $\mathrm{R} \mathrm{Cos}(\phi-\alpha)$ where $\mathrm{R}>0$ and $0 \leq \alpha \leq 90^{\circ}$.
