5. (a) Given the complex numbers
$$\begin{aligned}
& Z_{1}=2+3 J, Z_{2}=4-3 j \text { and } Z_{3}=1+4 j, \text { express } \\
& Z=\frac{Z_{1} Z_{2} Z_{3}}{Z_{1}+Z_{2}+Z_{3}} \text { in the form } a+j b .
\end{aligned}$$
(b) Find all the roots of the equation $Z^{3}-1-j \sqrt{3}=0$ in polar form.
(c) Given that $Z=-2-j$ is a root of the equation $Z^{4}+10 Z^{3}+39 Z^{2}+70 Z+50=0$ determine the other roots.
6. (a) Given that $M \operatorname{Cosh} 3 x+N \operatorname{Sinh} 3 x \equiv 7 e^{3 x}+6 e^{-3 x}$ determine the values of M and N .
(b) (i) Prove that
$$\operatorname{Sinh}^{-1}(x)=\ln \left(x+\sqrt{x^{2}+1}\right)$$
(ii) Hence evaluate $\operatorname{Sin}^{-1}(3)$ to three decimal places.
(c) Show that:
(i) $\frac{\operatorname{Sinh} x}{(\operatorname{Cosh} x-1)}=\operatorname{Coth} x+\operatorname{Cosech} x$
(ii) $\tanh 2 x=\frac{2 \tanh x}{1+\tanh ^{2} x}$
